Moura, M. O., & Ferreira, W. J. A. (2019). Os desafios da implantação da Base Nacional Comum Curricular (BNCC) no Brasil: uma revisão de literatura. Revista Brasileira de Educação de Jovens e Adultos, 1, 1, 142-162.
Os desafios da implantação da Base Nacional Comum Curricular (BNCC) no Brasil: uma revisão de literatura
The Base Nacional Comum Curricular (BNCC) is the first national curriculum to be proposed in Brazil. It was approved in 2018 and aims to guarantee the quality of education and the qualification of teachers and students in the country. This paper presents a systematic review of literature on the challenges of the implementation of the BNCC. The literature review was carried out in the bases of Scielo and Scielo Scopus, from 2010 to 2018. The search was carried out by using the key words: Base Nacional Comum Curricular (NCCB), education, challenges and challenges. The analysis of the articles presented, allowed to identify the following challenges: (i) the non-acceptance of the document by the political and academic community; (ii) the lack of agreement about the contents of the NCCB; (iii) the lack of knowledge of the teachers regarding the NCCB and the curriculum; (iv) the need to implement the NCCB; (v) the challenges to the implementation of the NCCB; and (vi) the proposal of the NCCB to the school. We conclude that the challenges of the implementation of the NCCB are many and of varied nature. We suggest the need to continue the discussion of the NCCB and the implementation of the NCCB.
